the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Matthew, your role in this game is villager.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Carolyn, Adrian\nLast words from Carolyn: Ladies and gentlemen, I am the Witch, and I have been eliminated on the first night. Before I go, I want to share some important information with you. Adrian was eliminated on the first night, and I used my poison on him. This suggests that Adrian was likely a werewolf, as he was the target of the werewolves' attack. Additionally, I noticed that Vera and Mark seemed overly eager to eliminate Adrian, which could indicate that they are also werewolves. Their behavior and quick decision to vote for Adrian's elimination were suspicious. Be cautious and gather more information before making any eliminations. Trust the Seer's information and work together to protect key players like the Seer and the Guard. Good luck, and may the village prevail.\nPlayer Carolyn has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayer Adrian has been eliminated from the game.\nChun's speech: Thank you, Carolyn, for your bravery and the important information you shared with us. I agree with you that Adrian was likely a werewolf, given the witch's use of poison on him. Your observations about Vera and Mark's behavior are also worth considering. They seemed overly eager to eliminate Adrian, which could indicate that they are either werewolves or very well-informed villagers. I believe we should be cautious and gather more information before making any eliminations. Let's work together to protect key players like the Seer and the Guard, and make sure we don't rush into anything. We need to be smart and strategic if we want to survive and eliminate the werewolves.\nFlora's speech: Thank you, Chun, for your insightful speech. I completely agree with you that Adrian was likely a werewolf, given the witch's use of poison on him. Your observations about Vera and Mark's behavior are also worth considering, but I think we should be cautious and gather more information before making any eliminations. Let's work together to protect key players like the Seer and the Guard, and make sure we don't rush into anything. We need to be smart and strategic if we want to survive and eliminate the werewolves. I believe it's important to focus on gathering more information and building trust within our group before we make any accusations.\nHelen's speech: Thank you, Carolyn, for your bravery and the important information you shared with us. I completely agree with Chun and Flora that Adrian was likely a werewolf, given the witch's use of poison on him. Their observations about Vera and Mark's behavior are also worth considering. They seemed overly eager to eliminate Adrian, which could indicate that they are either werewolves or very well-informed villagers. I believe we should be cautious and gather more information before making any eliminations. Let's work together to protect key players like the Seer and the Guard, and make sure we don't rush into anything. We need to be smart and strategic if we want to survive and eliminate the werewolves. I have gathered information that could be crucial to our survival, and I will share it with you as we continue to gather more evidence. Let's stay vigilant and work together to protect our village.\nMark's speech: Thank you for your speeches, Chun, Flora, and Helen. I completely agree with your